feat(notifications): notifications 2.0 double write (#55696)

This PR writes to the new notification tables when the
`organizations:notifications-double-write` flag is set. This way, after
we run the migration we can ensure that the new tables are in sync with
the old. Though we can turn the flag on before the migration to validate
functionality first.

chore(webhooks): Refactor file system for stripe webhooks (#11583)

Moving files, changing variable names and adding the region decorator to
the stripe webhook manager.

`getsentry/web/webhooks/` -> `getsentry/web/stripe/webhooks/`
`WebhookManager` -> `StripeWebhookManager`
`manager` -> `stripe_webhook_manager`

Pretty much just a semantic PR but we consume more webhooks in getsentry
than just Stripe (e.g. Provisioning), so now it follows the convention

feat(hybrid-cloud): Add Github Marketplace webhook parser  (#11581)

This PR adds a the github marketplace webhook parser. It catches
requests to the following:

- `/remote/github/marketplace/provision/` handle on default region
synchronously (US)
- `/remote/github/marketplace/purchase/` handle on control synchonrously
- `/temote/github/webhook/`
  - purchased: handle on default region synchronously (US)
- cancelled, or changed: can be forwarded to a specific region, after I
replicate the external_id column from PartnerAccount (future PR).
There's a TODO in the code to add this. For now, uses default region
(US)
  
Making these changes I also had to add the `GitHubIdentity` RPC service
so that the endpoints could be region-silo safe.

pullRequest.title: feat(hybrid-cloud): Add Github Marketplace webhook parser
pullRequest.message:
This PR adds a the github marketplace webhook parser. It catches requests to the following:

- `/remote/github/marketplace/provision/` handle on default region synchronously (US)
- `/remote/github/marketplace/purchase/` handle on control synchonrously
- `/temote/github/webhook/`
  - purchased: handle on default region synchronously (US)
  - cancelled, or changed:  can be forwarded to a specific region, after I replicate the external_id column from PartnerAccount (future PR). There's a TODO in the code to add this. For now, uses default region (US)
  
 Making these changes I also had to add the `GitHubIdentity` RPC service so that the endpoints could be region-silo safe.

lastCommit.message: ref(hybrid-cloud): Moves post-save handlers for subscription to use outboxes (#11466)

pullRequest.title: ref(hybrid-cloud): Moves post-save handlers for subscription to use outboxes
pullRequest.message:
Reworks the `handle_organization_alert_rules` and `flush_quota_cache_for_model` subscription on-save handlers to use outboxes to ensure at-least once delivery for both.

This allows us to queue these changes transactionally with less side-effects as well if the parent operation to subscription is rolled back for example.

**Note:** This relies on getsentry/sentry#55384 to merge before cross-db tests will pass.

feat(backup): Generate new UUIDs and secrets when needed (#55826)

UUIDs should always be unique (it's right in the name!). When we import
a `UUIDField`, we should generate a new UUID for it, and update all
relevant references.

Similarly, we enforce `ProjectKey` API token uniqueness. When importing
a colliding token, which will likely happen, we generate new API keys
for that project. This may break some user flows during cross-region
relocation, so there is a note to revisit this decision later.

Issue: getsentry/team-ospo#193
